          <th scope="col" style="padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; color: #94a3b8; font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase;">Root Cause</th>
          <th scope="col" style="padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; color: #94a3b8; font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase;">Remediation CLI Command</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; font-family: monospace; color: #f87171;">No GITHUB_TOKEN or missing results.json</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; color: #cbd5e1;">The container-only lane could not publish structured results, or the suite failed before writing its result payload.</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem;"><code style="color: #38bdf8; font-size: 0.78rem;">kubectl get secret -n argo github-token</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; font-family: monospace; color: #f87171;">results.json not found / Execution failed</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; color: #cbd5e1;">A container-only test lane failed before the summary step completed.</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem;"><code style="color: #38bdf8; font-size: 0.78rem;">just logs</code><br/><span style="font-size: 0.7rem; color: #64748b;">Identify the failing suite in the run-container-tests output.</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; font-family: monospace; color: #f59e0b;">Expected image-poll rerun never starts</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; color: #cbd5e1;">The digest may already be recorded in <code>image-polling-digests</code>, so the poller treats the image as already seen.</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem;"><code style="color: #38bdf8; font-size: 0.78rem;">kubectl get configmap -n argo image-polling-digests -o yaml</code><br/><span style="font-size: 0.7rem; color: #64748b;">Compare the stored digest with the latest workflow log before clearing state.</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; font-family: monospace; color: #ef4444;">FailedCreate: metadata.labels must be ≤63 chars</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; color: #cbd5e1;">Argo workflow generated a VM name that exceeds the Kubernetes label length limits.</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem;"><code style="color: #38bdf8; font-size: 0.78rem;">use workflow.name-item pattern</code><br/><span style="font-size: 0.7rem; color: #64748b;">Shorten test naming definitions in the YAML templates.</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);">
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; font-family: monospace; color: #94a3b8;">VM stuck in Terminating status</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem; color: #cbd5e1;">Virt-launcher pod is locked by system processes and needs manual termination.</td>
          <td style="padding: 0.75rem;"><code style="color: #38bdf8; font-size: 0.78rem;">kubectl delete pod -n bluefin-test ...</code></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h4 style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">How to Reproduce & Run Tests Locally</h4>
  <p>
    Bluefin operates as an atomic, image-based OS. You can replicate the exact dashboard BDD verification checks locally using the following steps:
  </p>
  <ol style="margin: 0; padding-left: 1.25rem; color: #64748b; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <li><strong>Verify Cluster Access:</strong> Run <code>just list-workflows</code> to confirm Argo connectivity and namespace visibility.</li>
    <li><strong>Sync Workflow Definitions:</strong> Execute <code>just argocd-sync</code> if you need the latest GitOps state before testing.</li>
    <li><strong>Container-Only Validation:</strong> Run <code>just run-tests-tag testing</code> or <code>just run-tests-tag lts-testing</code> to test the published bootc OCI image directly as a container.</li>
    <li><strong>Matrix Smoke Check:</strong> Run <code>just run-tests-matrix</code> when you want the default testing and lts-testing smoke pair.</li>
  </ol>

